9
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:22,370
in Xiamen, China.

10
00:00:22,370 --> 00:00:24,660
It’s a meeting between the world’s l

11
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:25,710
argest developing economies—

12
00:00:25,710 --> 00:00:29,800
Brazil, Russia, India, China, and South Africa.

13
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,190
Personally I think they should have

14
00:00:31,190 --> 00:00:32,679
gone with SBRIC

15
00:00:32,679 --> 00:00:34,010
or maybe BRISC.

16
00:00:34,010 --> 00:00:36,789
That’s BRISC, baby.

17
00:00:36,789 --> 00:00:39,230
Together, these five BRICS countries

18
00:00:39,230 --> 00:00:42,440
make up 40% of the world’s population,

19
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:44,700
25% of the world’s landmass,

20
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:47,699
and almost 30% of the global GDP.

21
00:00:47,699 --> 00:00:49,339
Now while you might be thinking:

22
00:00:49,339 --> 00:00:51,159
This BRICS Summit sounds like

23
