Almost as cool?

41
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,760
Now I understand why CCTV did that animation.

42
00:01:40,770 --> 00:01:42,730
So what did the real-life versions

43
00:01:42,730 --> 00:01:44,630
of those race car drivers discuss

44
00:01:44,630 --> 00:01:47,710
during their three-day extravaganza?

45
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:48,710
One thing,

46
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:49,950
as I mentioned earlier in the broadcast,

47
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:52,530
is that they’re all angry at North Korea

48
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:54,280
for trying to upstage their party

49
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,920
with a nuclear test.

50
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:58,500
But looming over the three day summit

51
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,810
was the intense rivalry smoldering

52
00:02:00,810 --> 00:02:03,230
between the two biggest countries:

53
00:02:03,230 --> 00:02:04,770
India and China.

54
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:06,210
For about 70 days,

55
00:02:06,210 --> 00:02:09,219
India and China were locked in a serious border
dispute

56
00:02:09,219 --> 00:02:12,459
that threatened to turn into full blown war.

57
00:02:12,459 --> 00:02:13,459
And by threatened,

58
00:02:13,459 --> 00:02:14,980
I mean—Chinese state-run media

59
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:17,140
was threatening war.

60
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:18,209
And that was just a symptom

61
00:02:18,209 --> 00:02:19,650
of much deeper tensions

62
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:21,599
between the two nations.

63
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,410
The dispute was eventually resolved,

64
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:25,390
with both sides saving face,

65
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:27,719
just in time for the BRICS summit.

66
00:02:27,719 --> 00:02:31,350
And the two leaders both seemed amicable enough...

67
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:34,060
But things are far from smooth between India
and China.

68
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:37,200
They’re still economic and political rivals.

69
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,099
Oh, and military rivals.

70
00:02:40,099 --> 00:02:41,800
On the Friday before the summit,

71
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:45,659
China held live fire drills in the Indian
Ocean.

72
00:02:45,659 --> 00:02:47,680
Or as the Chinese Communist Party calls it,

73
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,469
the “Southwest China Sea.”

74
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:51,019
I’m just kidding.

75
00:02:51,019 --> 00:02:52,739
I think.

76
00:02:52,739 --> 00:02:54,480
But speaking of territorial disputes,

77
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:57,120
those also made their way into the summit.

78
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:00,340
Xi Jinping was pushing his One Belt One Road
Initiative.

79
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:03,829
He says it will link China and the rest of
Eurasia together

80
00:03:03,829 --> 00:03:08,540
for mutual economic prosperity and high-speed
car chases.

81
00:03:08,540 --> 00:03:11,609
But India considers it a debt-fueled disaster

82
00:03:11,609 --> 00:03:13,689
that will see China surrounding India

83
00:03:13,689 --> 00:03:15,690
and threatening its sovereignty.

84
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:17,099
A huge part of the plan involves

85
00:03:17,099 --> 00:03:19,920
the China Pakistan Economic Corridor—

86
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:20,920
which would go through territory

87
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:24,610
that India disputes with Pakistan.

88
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:26,950
Pakistan is of course a major rival to India

89
00:03:26,950 --> 00:03:29,360
over more than just territory.

90
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,430
India considers Pakistan

91
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:32,280
a source of terrorism.

92
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,599
Yes, terrorism.

93
00:03:33,599 --> 00:03:34,599
That’s another point

94
00:03:34,599 --> 00:03:37,370
that China and India square off over.

95
00:03:37,370 --> 00:03:40,279
Since China is pretty buddy buddy with Pakistan,

96
00:03:40,279 --> 00:03:42,129
the Chinese regime has used its spot

97
00:03:42,129 --> 00:03:44,829
as permanent member on the UN security council

98
00:03:44,829 --> 00:03:47,430
to block India’s attempts to have the leader

99
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:49,499
of the Pakistan-based terrorist group

100
00:03:49,499 --> 00:03:50,889
Jaish-e-Mohammad

101
00:03:50,889 --> 00:03:53,010
put on a terror blacklist.

102
00:03:53,010 --> 00:03:55,170
Yes, China has blocked the leader

103
00:03:55,170 --> 00:03:57,230
of a terrorist organization

104
00:03:57,230 --> 00:03:59,659
from being labeled a terrorist.

105
00:03:59,659 --> 00:04:01,400
But India won a round on that front

106
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,870
at this BRICS Summit.

107
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,840
In the 43-page joint statement

108
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,379
put out during the summit,

109
00:04:06,379 --> 00:04:09,129
tackling terrorism was a key point.

110
00:04:09,129 --> 00:04:10,249
And it specifically called out

111
00:04:10,249 --> 00:04:11,650
Pakistan based groups

112
00:04:11,650 --> 00:04:13,150
like Lashkar-e-Taiba

113
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:14,650
and Jaish-e-Mohammad,

114
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:16,180
alongside ISIS and al-Qaida.

115
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:20,040
That may put a strain on China-Pakistan ties.

116
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:21,960
Another reason the Chinese regime

117
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,090
is concerned about India

118
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:25,620
is its ties to the United States.

119
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:28,450
Beijing is leery of being surrounded by US
allies,

120
00:04:28,450 --> 00:04:31,199
like South Korea, Japan, Australia, and India.

121
00:04:31,199 --> 00:04:32,680
So smoothing over recent tensions

122
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,949
to ensure India came to BRICS

123
00:04:34,949 --> 00:04:36,590
is part of a long term plan

124
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:37,740
to make India,

125
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:39,180
and all the other countries,

126
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:42,060
more reliant on China instead of the West.

127
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:44,620
A big part of that is the New Development
Bank.

128
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:47,740
It was started two years ago by the BRICS
countries.

129
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:51,030
The idea is to rival the World Bank and the
IMF.

130
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:52,840
The New Development Bank is equally funded

131
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,500
by all five BRICS countries:

132
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:58,400
Brazil, Russia, India, China, and South Africa.

133
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:01,210
And it will offer loans for projects in those
countries—

134
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:02,960
without all the strings attached

135
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:05,490
that Western countries tend to add.

136
00:05:05,490 --> 00:05:06,490
Worthless strings,

137
00:05:06,490 --> 00:05:07,710
like government transparency

138
00:05:07,710 --> 00:05:09,820
and human rights.

139
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:11,129
The New Development Bank is probably

140
00:05:11,129 --> 00:05:13,129
the most concrete thing to come out of

141
00:05:13,129 --> 00:05:15,449
the BRICS Summits in recent years.

142
00:05:15,449 --> 00:05:16,940
Each country has pledged

143
00:05:16,940 --> 00:05:19,050
$10 billion dollars to it so far.

144
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:20,800
The first project it funded

145
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:23,930
is a solar energy plant in China.

146
00:05:23,930 --> 00:05:25,479
And one of the next projects it will fund

147
00:05:25,479 --> 00:05:28,410
is a drinking water system in rural India.

148
00:05:28,410 --> 00:05:30,810
Of course China’s $10 billion investment

149
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,539
in the New Development Bank is small

150
00:05:32,539 --> 00:05:35,159
compared to the $120 billion

151
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:37,340
Xi Jinping pledged to his One Belt,

152
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:39,129
One Road initiative back in May.

153
00:05:39,129 --> 00:05:42,180
So he’s still giving priority to that.

154
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:43,419
But as much as the Chinese regime

155
00:05:43,419 --> 00:05:47,310
would like India to become economically dependent
on China,

156
00:05:47,310 --> 00:05:49,970
the plan may have backfired a bit.

157
00:05:49,970 --> 00:05:52,360
Because while Xi’s back was turned,

158
